Wheater its Java based configuration or xml base we are not haapy
in the Configuration part here we can use Something Call stereotype Annotation
with the help of that we can make our work so eassy

with the StereoType Annotation we can talk with Spring framework
with Our Class Metadata itself


and all the classes which we want to be managed by the Spring Framwork
we will add @Component Annotation and to tell Spring hey Search for those
Classes we will use @ComponentScan which will scan the those classes
for the Package we have those in

@Component("org.example.demo")
in Your Configuration class
Means we dont need to write anything in our Config File
